---

<Layout title="ToC Ch.2 — Nondeterminism" favicon="🔀">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/theory-of-computation/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to Theory of Computation</a>

    <h1>Nondeterminism</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Maheshwari &amp; Smid &middot; Ch. 2 &middot; <a href="https://cglab.ca/~michiel/TheoryOfComputation/">Introduction to Theory of Computation</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">A <strong>nondeterministic finite automaton</strong> (NFA) can be in multiple states at once. It guesses which path to take, and accepts if <em>any</em> path reaches an accepting state. NFAs are not more powerful than DFAs: the subset construction converts any NFA to an equivalent DFA.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- NFA definition -->
    <h3>NFA: multiple paths at once</h3>
    <p>An NFA is the same 5-tuple as a DFA, except the transition function maps to <em>sets</em> of states: &delta; : Q &times; (&Sigma; &cup; &#123;&epsilon;&#125;) &rarr; P(Q). At each step the machine can follow any transition, including &epsilon;-transitions that consume no input.</p>

    <!-- SVG: NFA with branching and epsilon -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 440 180" class="w-full max-w-lg" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- q0 -->
        <circle cx="60" cy="90" r="22" fill="none" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.6"/>
        <text x="60" y="95" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="13">q0</text>
        <!-- Start -->
        <line x1="10" y1="90" x2="35" y2="90" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
        <polygon points="36,90 28,85 28,95" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.5"/>
        <!-- q1 (upper branch) -->
        <circle cx="200" cy="40" r="22" fill="none" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.6"/>
        <text x="200" y="45" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="13">q1</text>
        <!-- q2 (lower branch) -->
        <circle cx="200" cy="140" r="22" fill="none" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.6"/>
        <text x="200" y="145" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="13">q2</text>
        <!-- q3 (accepting) -->
        <circle cx="360" cy="90" r="22" fill="none" stroke="#34d399" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.6"/>
        <circle cx="360" cy="90" r="18" fill="none" stroke="#34d399" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.6"/>
        <text x="360" y="95" text-anchor="middle" fill="#34d399" font-size="13">q3</text>
        <!-- q0 --a--> q1 -->
        <line x1="78" y1="75" x2="182" y2="52" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
        <polygon points="183,51 174,50 177,58" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.5"/>
        <text x="120" y="52" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="12" fill-opacity="0.5">a</text>
        <!-- q0 --epsilon--> q2 -->
        <line x1="78" y1="105" x2="182" y2="128" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
        <polygon points="183,129 174,122 177,130" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.5"/>
        <text x="120" y="132" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="12" fill-opacity="0.5" font-style="italic">&epsilon;</text>
        <!-- q1 --b--> q3 -->
        <line x1="218" y1="52" x2="342" y2="78" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
        <polygon points="343,79 334,74 336,82" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.5"/>
